  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Semantic Structure</h3>
    <p>The menu element conveys that its items are commands. Each <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> should contain a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;a&gt;</code> for proper interaction.</p>

    <h3>ARIA Roles</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>role="separator"</code> - Marks visual dividers between groups of items</li>
      <li><code>aria-label</code> - Use on icon-only buttons to describe the action</li>
      <li><code>aria-disabled</code> - For non-functional menu items</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Icon Buttons</h3>
    <p>When using icon-only buttons, always include an <code>aria-label</code> for screen reader users:</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Icon button with aria-label">{{ iconButtonCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Keyboard Navigation</h3>
    <p>Menu buttons receive standard keyboard focus. For more complex menu patterns with arrow key navigation, consider using ARIA menu roles or a JavaScript-enhanced component.</p>

